8:
Um, excuse me. Could you please let 
us through?
11:
"Could you pwease let us through?" 
Hah! I dunno... What do you boys 
think?
12:
Where are you lovebirds off to in such 
a hurry anyway? Off to have a good 
time?
13:
How about lettin' us tag along too? 
Whatcha say? Gahahaha!
18:
I can't guarantee whether you'll have 
a good time or not, however.
21: Hey... You makin' fun of us?
24:
Not at all. If you wish to join us, feel 
free to do so.
27: You're DEFINITELY makin' fun of us!
31:
Ahem! That isn't very GORGEOUS of 
you!
34:
You foolishly underestimate their 
strength with your vulgar behavior. 
And not only that...
38:
It's clear as day that you don't believe 
in yourselves! NOT gorgeous.
40:
What the hell are you goin' on about, 
lady? Keep your nose out of our busi—
44:
The name's Marguerite, pursuer of all 
things GORGEOUS. And don't you 
forget it!
54:
What provoked you to attack those 
men? They simply wanted to join us.
59:
So PURE! So HUMBLE! Truly... 
GORGEOUS! But you musn't let this 
way of thinking sully your beauty!
62:
Damn... you! Nobody gets away... 
with mockin'... me!
65:
Now look upon his fury—an ugly 
reflection of his twisted heart 
responding to your purity!
72:
Indeed! Self-loathing impedes his 
light within that surely once shone on 
the outside...
75:
Do you understand now? What's 
diminishing your light is none other 
than yourself!
84:
But you're a fool if you think such an 
unconfident fist could defeat me!
87: Allow me to show you TRUE beauty!
97:
Right there! Do you feel it now? 
Beautiful, GORGEOUS camaraderie!
98:
Now stand proudly and gorgeously! 
You too can be beautiful—you only 
need to believe!
101:
Believe me, boys, you'll be knockin' em 
dead in no time!
105:
And on that note... Can either of you 
two tell me where I am?
111:
I thought for sure I'd sunk to the 
bottom of the sea... But somehow 
I ended up on an unfamiliar rooftop.
114:
I never thought I'd end up meeting 
travelers from another world! I truly 
am a blessed woman.
117: Wait, you believe me? Just like that?
120:
I just so happen to be aquainted with 
quite a few drifters myself from all the 
seas, if you catch my drift. Nothing 
I haven't heard before, darling.
122:
Besides, I FEEL that I can trust you! 
What more do you need than that, 
really?
126:
Do you mean to say you would like to 
accompany us?
129:
I'm certain we can find a way for you 
to return to your world. 
That, and... I am curious to learn more 
about you.
134:
Who am I to refuse an invitation from 
such a GORGEOUS beauty! Yes, yes... I gladly accept!
136:
I'd be simply DELIGHTED to tell you 
more about not only myself, but 
everything that makes our world 
GORGEOUS!
138:
But I must warn you—not everyone 
has what it takes to appreciate TRUE 
beauty, for it comes in all forms and 
shapes!
145:
Yes, YES! Another GORGEOUS answer, 
darling!
150:
*sigh* We've got a real card on our 
hands this time, don't we?
